      "acceptanceCriteria": "All uncertain input parameters must be characterized with probability distributions derived from physiological literature; input uncertainty must be propagated through Monte Carlo sampling to hemolysis QoI.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ performed with distributions assigned to inlet flow rate, rotational speed, and blood viscosity based on literature ranges. Hemolysis power-law coefficients treated as fixed nominal values despite known inter-study variability. Input uncertainty partially characterized. Achieved level 2 against required level 5. Note: sensitivity analysis to identify which inputs dominate output variance was scoped for a future phase and is not included in this submission.",
